description: PHP-specific guidelines for the package internals. Auto-attached to any edit under src/, routes/, config/, or database/stubs/.
globs: src/**/*.php,routes/**/*.php,config/**/*.php,database/stubs/**/*
alwaysApply: false
---

When editing any of these files, the contract-driven design is in play.
Read the relevant detail file in `.ai/`:

- Architecture / where-things-go: `.ai/guidelines/package-architecture.md`
- Contract rules: `.ai/guidelines/contract-purity.md`
- API surface: `.ai/guidelines/api-design.md`
- Schema rules (only if touching `database/stubs/`): `.ai/guidelines/database-schema.md`

## Quick checks before committing

```bash
# No leaks of app-namespaced classes
rg -n '\\App\\\\Models\\\\' src/ routes/ config/ database/stubs/

# Routes still register
php artisan route:list | grep nova-chat
```

If you're adding a feature, follow the playbook in
`.ai/skills/add-package-feature/SKILL.md` end-to-end before opening the
PR.
